body:
**Description**
I'm trying to get a gray8 image from the pixel buffer which without encoded.
Unfortunately, the result seems get a bgra8888 image.



**Code**
`     

            var imageInfo = new SKImageInfo(size.Width, size.Height, SKColorType.Gray8);
            //I'm pretty sure the picData is gray8 rows' pixel without encode
            using (var data = SKData.CreateCopy(picData))
            {
                try
                {
                    using (var image = SKImage.FromPixelCopy(imageInfo, data.Data, size.Width))
                    {
                        // the bitmap become 4 bytes per pixel, color type become bgra8888
                        var bitmap = SKBitmap.FromImage(image); 
                        using (var skData = image.Encode(SKEncodedImageFormat.Jpeg, 100))
                        {
                        }
                    }
                }
                catch (Exception e)
                {
                    Console.WriteLine(e);
                    throw;
                }
            }`


**Expected Behavior**

Get a gray8 bitmap, 1 byte per pixel.

**Actual Behavior**

Get a bgra8888 bitmap, 4 byte per pixel.

**Basic Information**

- Version with issue:  <!-- -->1.68.0 
- Last known good version:  <!--   -->Don't know
- IDE:  <!--  -->Visual Studio 2017 Version 15.7.1
- Platform Target Frameworks: <!--  -->.net core 2.0
- Windows Classic:  <!-- -->Win10
